WEBVTT

1
00:00:30.767 --> 00:00:32.064
Here it comes!

2
00:00:32.702 --> 00:00:33.498
Huh?

3
00:00:34.571 --> 00:00:37.062
What the...? Hm?

4
00:00:38.308 --> 00:00:41.004
- Makoto, just throw the ball!
- Hmm...


5
00:00:41.077 --> 00:00:44.046
Hey, did you just hear something?

6
00:00:44.748 --> 00:00:45.874
You hear something?

7
00:00:46.082 --> 00:00:47.140
Hear what?

8
00:00:48.251 --> 00:00:49.718
What the...?

9
00:00:51.454 --> 00:00:52.751
Hey, Makoto!

10
00:00:57.260 --> 00:00:58.420
Here it comes!

11
00:00:59.663 --> 00:01:02.063
- There!
- W-Whoa... Yeah!


12
00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:05.097
Ah! Damn!

13
00:01:06.536 --> 00:01:07.594
All right!

14
00:01:08.004 --> 00:01:09.301
So yesterday...

15
00:01:09.372 --> 00:01:11.340
- Huh?
... pudding...


16
00:01:12.375 --> 00:01:14.343
...I missed out on pudding.

17
00:01:14.411 --> 00:01:16.242
What happened to the pudding?

18
00:01:16.313 --> 00:01:18.281
I bet your little sister beat you
to it again.


19
00:01:21.651 --> 00:01:24.484
I was purposely saving it.

20
00:01:24.554 --> 00:01:27.523
How dare she eat it,
that stupid little sister of mine!


21
00:01:27.591 --> 00:01:29.024
Watch it...! There!

22
00:01:30.227 --> 00:01:32.855
Aww, I did it again.

23
00:01:33.697 --> 00:01:34.755
Sis?

24
00:01:34.831 --> 00:01:35.695
Huh?

25
00:01:35.765 --> 00:01:37.426
- Sis?
- What?


26
00:01:42.205 --> 00:01:44.537
What the...? Huh?

27
00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:46.542
Makoto! Makoto!

28
00:01:46.910 --> 00:01:47.877
What?

29
00:01:48.211 --> 00:01:50.111
Look up! Above you!

30
00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:51.306
Up?

31
00:01:55.285 --> 00:01:56.445
Ow!

32
00:01:56.519 --> 00:01:59.511
Th
-That hurt...

33
00:02:10.200 --> 00:02:11.929
It's about time you got up.

34
00:02:13.837 --> 00:02:21.403
The Girl Who Leapt Through Time

35
00:02:21.978 --> 00:02:24.105
- Do you know what today is?
- Why'd you turn off the alarm?!


36
00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:26.648
You turned it off yourself!
I'm off now!


37
00:02:26.716 --> 00:02:29.742
- It's July 13, which is a "Nice Day".
- You have a good day.


38
00:02:29.819 --> 00:02:31.514
- What's a "Nice Day"?
- I'm in trouble!


39
00:02:31.588 --> 00:02:34.182
Seven, one, three could be
read as "Na-I-Su".


40
00:02:34.257 --> 00:02:36.225
You're finally up, Makoto?

41
00:02:36.293 --> 00:02:38.523
- G'morning, Dad.
- Oh, uh...


42
00:02:44.367 --> 00:02:45.391
G'morning.

43
00:02:45.468 --> 00:02:48.403
- I'm outta here!
- Oh, Makoto! Hang on!


44
00:02:48.471 --> 00:02:49.460
What?

45
00:02:49.539 --> 00:02:52.133
Take this to your Auntie Witch
after school.


46
00:02:52.208 --> 00:02:56.110
- Tell her it's from Grandma.
- No way! I don't want to take that to school.


47
00:02:56.479 --> 00:02:57.844
- And...
- Huh?


48
00:02:57.914 --> 00:03:00.815
Maybe you can ask her when
she's going to get married.


49
00:03:00.884 --> 00:03:02.408
- Sure.
- Good.


50
00:03:02.485 --> 00:03:04.248
I'm off!

51
00:03:06.056 --> 00:03:07.546
Have a good day.

52
00:03:19.936 --> 00:03:21.836
Oh, hi, Mako!

53
00:03:22.005 --> 00:03:23.404
Good morning!

54
00:03:41.624 --> 00:03:44.787
Sorry about the ruckus
every morning.


55
00:03:48.932 --> 00:03:51.230
- Chiaki!
- Hey, Makoto.


56
00:03:51.301 --> 00:03:53.769
You should work more time
into your schedule.


57
00:03:53.837 --> 00:03:55.532
You're telling me?!

58
00:03:55.605 --> 00:03:57.334
I bet you fell
back asleep after the alarm.

59
00:03:57.407 --> 00:03:58.271
Shut up!

60
00:03:58.341 --> 00:04:00.809
- What's in the basket?
- Nothing!


61
00:04:00.877 --> 00:04:02.435
Come on. Tell me.

62
00:04:06.583 --> 00:04:08.744
Once again, in the nick of time.

63
00:04:08.818 --> 00:04:11.286
It'd be more refreshing
if you'd just come late.


64
00:04:11.354 --> 00:04:12.685
You're early, Kousuke.

65
00:04:12.756 --> 00:04:14.917
Did you jerk off properly this morning?

66
00:04:14.991 --> 00:04:17.824
Shut up.
You guys are always too late.


67
00:04:17.894 --> 00:04:20.886
- It's not in the nick of time. Look.
- Huh?


68
00:04:21.164 --> 00:04:22.791
Are we lucky or what?

69
00:04:22.866 --> 00:04:24.458
I'm the lucky one.

70
00:04:24.534 --> 00:04:26.434
Huh? What'd you mean?

71
00:04:26.503 --> 00:04:29.666
You tend to say you're out of luck
when you're unlucky.


72
00:04:29.739 --> 00:04:32.003
But I figured that
had nothing to do with me.


73
00:04:32.075 --> 00:04:34.339
If anything, luck tends
to be on my side.

74
00:04:34.411 --> 00:04:37.744
Now, why do you think
your teacher was late today?


75
00:04:37.814 --> 00:04:39.042
A mini quiz?

76
00:04:39.115 --> 00:04:40.810
Yes, Hayakawa. Correct!

77
00:04:41.184 --> 00:04:42.651
What?!

78
00:04:47.424 --> 00:04:50.689
Nevertheless, luck still tends
to be on my side.


79
00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:52.751
I also have good instincts too.

80
00:04:52.829 --> 00:04:54.990
Thanks to that, my grades are okay.

81
00:04:55.065 --> 00:04:58.592
I'm not exactly a brain,
but I'm not an idiot either.


82
00:04:58.668 --> 00:05:00.636
You have five minutes left.

83
00:05:01.704 --> 00:05:02.500
Huh?

84
00:05:02.572 --> 00:05:04.540
I'm not an idiot...

85
00:05:06.609 --> 00:05:08.577
You have five minutes left.

86
00:05:08.645 --> 00:05:10.670
This is actually an exception.

87
00:05:10.747 --> 00:05:12.738
I'm not particularly
adept at things...


88
00:05:12.816 --> 00:05:15.842
...but I'm not so clumsy
that people laugh at me.


89
00:05:17.087 --> 00:05:18.554
Looking back...

90
00:05:18.621 --> 00:05:21.784
...I don't recall having too many
mess ups that I cringe about.


91
00:05:23.193 --> 00:05:24.182
Ow! Hot!

92
00:05:28.731 --> 00:05:31.825
What're you doing, idiot?!
Get the fire extinguisher! Hurry!


93
00:05:31.901 --> 00:05:33.129
Uh, yeah, right away!

94
00:05:33.203 --> 00:05:35.171
That was also an exception.

95
00:05:35.238 --> 00:05:37.968
- Are you all right?
- I singed my bangs a bit.


96
00:05:38.041 --> 00:05:41.943
Normally I'm pretty careful,
so I've never been badly injured.


97
00:05:42.212 --> 00:05:45.545
And I'm careful not to get involved
in complicated social situations.


98
00:05:49.385 --> 00:05:51.216
H
- Hey!

99
00:05:51.788 --> 00:05:53.346
Aww!

100
00:05:54.057 --> 00:05:56.218
What're you doing?! Come on!

101
00:06:09.806 --> 00:06:11.034
Look, you!

102
00:06:11.441 --> 00:06:14.444
- Oh? What's this?
- Blood type horoscopes have nothing to do with this.


103
00:06:14.477 --> 00:06:15.501
- Hold it, you!
- Blood type horoscopes have nothing to do with this.


104
00:06:15.578 --> 00:06:18.547
But it says they're not compatible.
Could be dicey.


105
00:06:18.615 --> 00:06:22.051
Whether it's dicey or not
is up to her to decide.


106
00:06:22.118 --> 00:06:23.142
What?

107
00:06:24.220 --> 00:06:30.126
Mathematics II Mini Quiz
"Let's try harder next time!"


108
00:06:30.161 --> 00:06:31.093
Makoto.

109
00:06:31.261 --> 00:06:31.989
What?

110
00:06:32.061 --> 00:06:34.130
Liberal Arts/Sciences Are you
going with liberal arts or sciences?


111
00:06:34.164 --> 00:06:36.499
Liberal Arts/Sciences -
Haven't decided. You? - Not yet.


112
00:06:36.533 --> 00:06:37.867
Liberal Arts/Sciences
Thank goodness.


113
00:06:37.901 --> 00:06:40.203
Liberal Arts/Sciences It's not
something to decide quickly.


114
00:06:40.236 --> 00:06:42.238
Liberal Arts/Sciences
You can't tell the future after all.


115
00:06:42.272 --> 00:06:44.607
Liberal Arts/Sciences
It never ends.


116
00:06:44.642 --> 00:06:45.073
Liberal Arts/Sciences

117
00:06:45.108 --> 00:06:46.837
Liberal Arts/Sciences
Hey, Makoto!


118
00:06:46.910 --> 00:06:48.878
How much longer are you gonna be?

119
00:06:48.945 --> 00:06:50.879
Then come and help me!

120
00:06:50.947 --> 00:06:52.414
You've gotta be kidding.

121
00:06:53.483 --> 00:06:54.950
Just hurry it up.

122
00:06:55.018 --> 00:06:55.985
Yeah.

123
00:06:58.821 --> 00:07:01.255
I wonder what Chiaki's
going to choose.


124
00:07:01.324 --> 00:07:03.815
Sciences, I bet.
He's not good with kanji.


125
00:07:03.893 --> 00:07:05.622
And he's amazing in math.

126
00:07:05.695 --> 00:07:08.755
But that's it.
Why bring up Chiaki anyways?


127
00:07:08.831 --> 00:07:11.561
Hey, someone's left
the hand-in notebooks here.


128
00:07:11.634 --> 00:07:13.124
Who's in charge of them?

129
00:07:13.469 --> 00:07:15.869
- Who is it?
- It's you!


130
00:07:18.408 --> 00:07:19.773
What a hassle...

131
00:07:36.726 --> 00:07:37.624
There!

132
00:07:39.696 --> 00:07:40.492
Huh?

133
00:07:46.069 --> 00:07:48.697
Time waits for no one.

134
00:07:51.507 --> 00:07:52.474
Hm?

135
00:08:30.747 --> 00:08:31.714
Huh?

136
00:08:37.153 --> 00:08:38.211
What the...?

137
00:08:38.921 --> 00:08:39.888
Hm?

138
00:08:47.230 --> 00:08:50.199
It sounded like
someone was here.


139
00:08:55.371 --> 00:08:56.338
Uh...

140
00:08:56.739 --> 00:08:57.899
Huh?!

141
00:08:58.508 --> 00:08:59.566
Hmm...

142
00:09:03.046 --> 00:09:04.536
A locked room...

143
00:09:04.614 --> 00:09:05.410
Huh?

144
00:09:10.720 --> 00:09:11.846
What's that?

145
00:10:51.988 --> 00:10:54.923
Are you an idiot or what?!
You're killing me!


146
00:10:54.991 --> 00:10:56.322
You're laughing too much.

147
00:10:56.392 --> 00:10:58.019
Yeah. You're laughing too much.

148
00:10:58.094 --> 00:11:00.824
- But it's just so funny!
- It's not funny.


149
00:11:00.897 --> 00:11:03.024
Wanna get a CT scan
at my dad's clinic?


150
00:11:03.099 --> 00:11:04.999
- I'm fine, all right?
- Be careful.


151
00:11:05.067 --> 00:11:06.796
Something might happen again.

152
00:11:06.869 --> 00:11:09.303
Nothing will happen.
I don't need the hassle.


153
00:11:09.372 --> 00:11:11.738
But people don't just collapse
for no reason.


154
00:11:11.808 --> 00:11:13.105
It's not for no reason!

155
00:11:13.176 --> 00:11:14.336
There was someone there!

156
00:11:14.410 --> 00:11:16.071
- Someone?
- Like who?


157
00:11:16.245 --> 00:11:18.213
Well...

158
00:11:18.381 --> 00:11:21.441
Why would I play a prank on you
and make you fall?


159
00:11:21.517 --> 00:11:22.779
Well...

160
00:11:22.852 --> 00:11:24.513
So I'm the culprit?

161
00:11:26.956 --> 00:11:28.924
Then, who could it have been?

162
00:11:32.495 --> 00:11:34.554
It sure is baking hot.

163
00:11:34.630 --> 00:11:36.723
It's almost summer vacation.
Suck it up!


164
00:11:36.799 --> 00:11:38.460
That's right! Summer vacation!

165
00:11:38.534 --> 00:11:40.434
Let's go somewhere,
the three of us!


166
00:11:40.503 --> 00:11:42.801
- Like where?
- We can go to a night game.


167
00:11:42.872 --> 00:11:45.864
We went last month.
That's all you want to do.


168
00:11:45.942 --> 00:11:47.933
- Then where?
- Like the beach.


169
00:11:48.010 --> 00:11:49.443
Too hot.

170
00:11:49.512 --> 00:11:52.481
Then, how about a fireworks festival?
We can wear yukatas.


171
00:11:52.548 --> 00:11:54.140
I don't have one.

172
00:11:54.217 --> 00:11:56.151
Where do you want to go, Kousuke?

173
00:11:57.019 --> 00:11:58.680
- The library.
- What?!


174
00:11:58.754 --> 00:12:00.051
I'll keep to my studies.

175
00:12:00.122 --> 00:12:03.523
If you keep studying in this heat,
you'll turn into an idiot.


176
00:12:03.593 --> 00:12:05.356
You guys don't study enough.

177
00:12:05.428 --> 00:12:07.658
Yeah, but I'm not
going into medicine.


178
00:12:07.730 --> 00:12:09.288
Then, what are you
going to do?


179
00:12:09.365 --> 00:12:10.332
Huh?

180
00:12:11.133 --> 00:12:13.363
Hmm... I'll become a hotel tycoon.

181
00:12:13.436 --> 00:12:14.232
Uh, what?

182
00:12:14.303 --> 00:12:15.702
Or maybe an oil tycoon.

183
00:12:15.771 --> 00:12:18.069
You've gotta think
about this seriously.


184
00:12:20.076 --> 00:12:23.568
Hey, what are you
going to do, Chiaki?


185
00:12:23.646 --> 00:12:24.613
Me?

186
00:12:25.781 --> 00:12:27.043
I'll...

187
00:12:28.284 --> 00:12:29.114
Ow!

188
00:12:31.454 --> 00:12:33.615
You guys need to get serious.

189
00:12:34.557 --> 00:12:36.184
Huh? Going home already?

190
00:12:36.259 --> 00:12:38.921
I forgot my mom wanted me
to do something.


191
00:12:38.995 --> 00:12:41.156
Huh? Don't be such a party pooper.

192
00:12:41.230 --> 00:12:43.255
So, I'm stuck hanging
with this guy alone?


193
00:12:43.332 --> 00:12:44.629
Well, see ya later!

194
00:12:44.700 --> 00:12:46.668
Hey. Hey!

195
00:12:48.404 --> 00:12:51.464
- Let's go!
- But the elves are coming out soon!


196
00:12:51.541 --> 00:12:52.974
Good heavens...

197
00:12:54.143 --> 00:12:55.110
Hm?

198
00:12:55.811 --> 00:12:57.904
Hey! Watch where you're going!

199
00:12:57.980 --> 00:12:59.080
I'm sorry!

200
00:12:59.115 --> 00:13:01.015
Kuranose Shopping Arcade

201
00:13:05.855 --> 00:13:06.651
Huh?

202
00:13:08.858 --> 00:13:10.325
If this was just like...

203
00:13:11.594 --> 00:13:14.222
If this was just like any other day...

204
00:13:14.297 --> 00:13:17.095
...there wouldn't have been
any problems.


205
00:13:17.166 --> 00:13:18.463
But...

206
00:13:19.802 --> 00:13:20.598
Huh?!

207
00:13:21.671 --> 00:13:23.639
- What?!
- I had forgotten...


208
00:13:23.706 --> 00:13:25.503
...that today was my worst day.

209
00:13:25.575 --> 00:13:26.701
What?!

210
00:13:33.683 --> 00:13:35.275
No!

211
00:13:35.551 --> 00:13:36.677
No!

212
00:13:55.371 --> 00:13:58.863
I can't believe this is happening,
but I'm going to die.


213
00:13:59.609 --> 00:14:01.201
This is my last day.

214
00:14:01.644 --> 00:14:05.205
If I knew this was going to happen,
I would've gotten up earlier.


215
00:14:05.281 --> 00:14:08.409
I wouldn't have slept in,
and I wouldn't have been late.


216
00:14:08.484 --> 00:14:10.816
I would've fried that
tempura better.


217
00:14:10.886 --> 00:14:13.855
And I wouldn't have been
slammed into by some idiot.


218
00:14:14.724 --> 00:14:18.353
I thought today was
supposed to be a "Nice Day".


219
00:14:30.373 --> 00:14:33.206
Ow...

220
00:14:34.176 --> 00:14:36.644
Hey! Where were you looking?!

221
00:14:37.613 --> 00:14:41.174
I want to hear an apology!
Apologize now!


222
00:14:43.119 --> 00:14:44.780
Uh, I'm sorry!

223
00:14:44.854 --> 00:14:47.288
Do you know why you have eyes?

224
00:14:47.356 --> 00:14:50.223
So you can see
where you're going. Got it?!


225
00:14:50.292 --> 00:14:52.283
Y
- Yes, I'm very sorry!

226
00:14:52.528 --> 00:14:54.018
Good heavens...!

227
00:14:55.698 --> 00:14:57.791
Hey, Mom. Look.

228
00:14:57.867 --> 00:14:58.663
Huh?

229
00:14:59.035 --> 00:15:01.026
Oh, my. It's already that time?

230
00:15:01.103 --> 00:15:01.899
Huh?

231
00:15:11.380 --> 00:15:12.711
Hm? How come?

232
00:15:17.286 --> 00:15:18.082
How come?!

233
00:15:38.607 --> 00:15:39.596
Hello?

234
00:15:41.644 --> 00:15:43.077
Miss Yoshiyama?

235
00:15:56.792 --> 00:15:59.659
"White Plum and Two Camellias" This painting is temporarily
unavailable for display due to restoration. Tokyo Metropolitan Museum


236
00:16:01.564 --> 00:16:03.930
Now, take it easy.
She'll be right down.


237
00:16:03.999 --> 00:16:04.988
Makoto!

238
00:16:05.501 --> 00:16:06.593
Auntie!

239
00:16:07.570 --> 00:16:09.003
Auntie Witch!

240
00:16:11.874 --> 00:16:14.809
Am I alive?!
I am alive, right?!


241
00:16:15.277 --> 00:16:17.711
There's nothing strange about me, right?

242
00:16:18.280 --> 00:16:20.248
Hmm...

243
00:16:20.950 --> 00:16:23.350
There's something strange
about your bangs.


244
00:16:24.587 --> 00:16:26.555
That was a time leap.

245
00:16:26.722 --> 00:16:27.848
Time leap?!

246
00:16:28.457 --> 00:16:31.290
- You were about to be hit by a train, right?
- Yeah.


247
00:16:31.360 --> 00:16:33.726
- After being thrown off your bike?
- Yeah!


248
00:16:33.796 --> 00:16:37.061
But when you came to,
you had gone back a few minutes?


249
00:16:37.133 --> 00:16:39.761
- That's right!
- That's what you call a time leap.


250
00:16:39.835 --> 00:16:43.202
- You see, time can never be reversed.
- Never be reversed?


251
00:16:43.272 --> 00:16:45.331
- Time itself doesn't go back.
- Hm.


252
00:16:45.407 --> 00:16:48.467
So what went back in time
was you yourself.


253
00:16:48.544 --> 00:16:51.877
It means you leapt back in time
and returned to the past.


254
00:16:53.182 --> 00:16:54.149
Really?

255
00:16:54.517 --> 00:16:56.212
It's not that unusual.

256
00:16:56.285 --> 00:16:59.584
It happens to a lot of girls
around your age.


257
00:17:02.024 --> 00:17:04.390
No way. No way.
That never happens.


258
00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:06.223
It happened to me.

259
00:17:06.295 --> 00:17:07.785
What? Are you serious?

260
00:17:07.863 --> 00:17:10.855
