656
00:40:57.225 --> 00:40:59.193
I wonder what it was?

657
00:41:02.396 --> 00:41:05.490
Hurry, let's go!
They're going to sell out!


658
00:41:05.566 --> 00:41:08.763
Umm, I'm not feeling
very good today.


659
00:41:08.836 --> 00:41:10.269
What?! You want to go
to the nurse's office?


660
00:41:10.338 --> 00:41:12.738
Oh! Uh, I'm fine. I'll be okay.

661
00:41:35.963 --> 00:41:40.832
- Let's hurry! This is something to see!
- What is it?


662
00:41:41.202 --> 00:41:43.670
- This way, this way!
- What's going on?


663
00:41:54.682 --> 00:41:56.309
Stop it, Takase!

664
00:41:57.918 --> 00:42:00.648
You're the ones that didn't stop
when I asked you to!


665
00:42:00.988 --> 00:42:03.149
All right! We were wrong!

666
00:42:03.224 --> 00:42:05.419
Then why'd you do it
in the first place?


667
00:42:05.493 --> 00:42:07.358
- That guy's lost it.
- Did someone call a teacher?


668
00:42:07.428 --> 00:42:08.895
Hey, check this out!

669
00:42:09.897 --> 00:42:11.387
Stop that, Takase!

670
00:42:11.666 --> 00:42:12.860
Takase!

671
00:42:16.404 --> 00:42:18.201
Konno!

672
00:42:18.606 --> 00:42:21.404
Did you just order me?!

673
00:42:21.909 --> 00:42:23.467
N
- No, I didn't!

674
00:42:23.644 --> 00:42:25.202
You did, too!

675
00:42:29.684 --> 00:42:31.208
Huh?! What?!

676
00:42:31.919 --> 00:42:36.583
W
- Why?! Damn! Damn! D
-Damn!

677
00:42:37.992 --> 00:42:40.358
- Hey! Stop it!
- Enough!


678
00:42:40.428 --> 00:42:42.692
- Takase!
- S-Stop...


679
00:42:42.763 --> 00:42:43.730
Watch out!

680
00:42:44.832 --> 00:42:45.799
Takase!

681
00:42:58.446 --> 00:42:59.538
Chiaki!

682
00:43:01.515 --> 00:43:02.482
Chiaki!

683
00:43:17.231 --> 00:43:18.698
- Are you okay?
- Yuri!


684
00:43:18.766 --> 00:43:20.859
- I heard that hit her big time!
- What year is she?


685
00:43:20.935 --> 00:43:22.527
Hurry, call a teacher!

686
00:43:22.603 --> 00:43:25.731
I- It wasn't my fault!
It wasn't my fault...!


687
00:43:26.073 --> 00:43:29.167
- Yuri! Yuri!
- Are you okay? Yuri!


688
00:43:41.122 --> 00:43:44.023
Don't cry. It's not that bad.

689
00:43:44.458 --> 00:43:46.483
What if it leaves a scar?

690
00:43:47.828 --> 00:43:50.797
If that happens,
I'll deal with it somehow.


691
00:43:51.565 --> 00:43:53.260
Deal with it somehow?

692
00:43:53.334 --> 00:43:54.858
I'll deal with it somehow.

693
00:44:08.549 --> 00:44:10.210
No boys allowed.

694
00:44:10.284 --> 00:44:11.683
Does it hurt?

695
00:44:11.986 --> 00:44:13.078
Yeah.

696
00:44:13.154 --> 00:44:15.145
- Let's see.
- No.


697
00:44:15.222 --> 00:44:16.189
Come on.

698
00:44:18.058 --> 00:44:19.025
Thanks.

699
00:44:27.301 --> 00:44:28.928
I'm sorry, seriously!

700
00:44:29.003 --> 00:44:30.834
Huh?! But, why?!

701
00:44:30.905 --> 00:44:32.736
I said I'm really sorry.

702
00:44:33.374 --> 00:44:37.140
Man, who takes a girl to a night game
on their first date?


703
00:44:37.578 --> 00:44:39.944
I thought the three of us were going!

704
00:44:40.014 --> 00:44:41.811
I was looking forward to it!

705
00:44:42.450 --> 00:44:44.748
Look, I feel bad about it, all right?

706
00:44:44.819 --> 00:44:47.287
Hayakawa said a night game
would be fine.


707
00:44:47.354 --> 00:44:49.413
So, are you gonna go out with her?

708
00:44:49.490 --> 00:44:50.957
- Of course.
- What?!


709
00:44:51.025 --> 00:44:51.992
Ow!

710
00:44:52.993 --> 00:44:54.426
You all right, Makoto?

711
00:44:54.495 --> 00:44:57.123
- Are you serious?
- You're saying I can't?


712
00:44:59.433 --> 00:45:03.995
Well, what can I say? Yuri gets
my tastes. You know what I mean?


713
00:45:04.805 --> 00:45:06.272
Well, good for you!

714
00:45:06.941 --> 00:45:10.274
Hey! Idiot!
Where are you throwing the ball?!


715
00:45:15.483 --> 00:45:16.745
I'm home!

716
00:45:19.253 --> 00:45:22.222
- Huh? Where's the rice?
- I'm making some more.


717
00:45:22.289 --> 00:45:24.621
- Why?
- Sis ate it all.


718
00:45:25.526 --> 00:45:26.322
Aww!

719
00:45:26.961 --> 00:45:31.125
What's with that guy?
After telling me he liked me!


720
00:45:47.481 --> 00:45:49.472
I almost drowned!

721
00:45:49.950 --> 00:45:52.612
Huh? Huh? Hm?

722
00:45:55.256 --> 00:45:56.484
What is this?

723
00:45:59.927 --> 00:46:01.292
Ninety?

724
00:46:17.912 --> 00:46:19.243
Makoto!

725
00:46:20.080 --> 00:46:22.048
Ow! Let go!

726
00:46:22.583 --> 00:46:24.380
I think we lost this one.

727
00:46:24.451 --> 00:46:26.646
She's pulled one over on us,
that's for sure.


728
00:46:26.720 --> 00:46:28.688
The world is full of deceit.

729
00:46:33.761 --> 00:46:36.628
I guess with just the two of us,
we can only toss the ball.


730
00:46:36.697 --> 00:46:38.597
Let's drag Chiaki with us tomorrow.

731
00:46:38.666 --> 00:46:40.327
That's not fair to Yuri.

732
00:46:40.401 --> 00:46:44.167
If I tell him that you're feeling lonely,
I bet he'd come.


733
00:46:45.005 --> 00:46:46.734
But I'm not lonely.

734
00:46:47.708 --> 00:46:51.269
Didn't Chiaki go with Hayakawa
because you turned him down?


735
00:46:51.345 --> 00:46:52.903
I didn't turn him down!

736
00:46:52.980 --> 00:46:53.969
Really?

737
00:46:54.048 --> 00:46:55.913
What's that supposed to mean?!

738
00:46:57.284 --> 00:46:58.478
Oh, boy...

739
00:46:58.719 --> 00:47:02.177
What about you?
Why don't you get a girlfriend?


740
00:47:02.523 --> 00:47:04.423
If I got a girlfriend...

741
00:47:04.725 --> 00:47:06.693
...then you'd end up alone.

742
00:47:12.299 --> 00:47:15.132
I thought you fancied Kousuke.

743
00:47:15.603 --> 00:47:19.505
Isn't it always Kousuke that helps you
when you're having problems?


744
00:47:19.573 --> 00:47:21.871
Kousuke's always there for anyone.

745
00:47:22.042 --> 00:47:24.010
Why don't you go out with him?

746
00:47:24.078 --> 00:47:26.569
- Why would you suggest that?
- Like I said before...


747
00:47:26.647 --> 00:47:29.844
...if it doesn't work out,
you can always go back to what it was.


748
00:47:29.917 --> 00:47:31.646
I would never do that.

749
00:47:31.719 --> 00:47:32.481
Why not?

750
00:47:32.553 --> 00:47:34.646
Toying with people's feelings...

751
00:47:34.722 --> 00:47:36.485
Can't do such a terrible thing?

752
00:47:36.557 --> 00:47:37.353
Huh?

753
00:47:37.424 --> 00:47:40.552
Since you've been able to
go back into the past...


754
00:47:40.628 --> 00:47:43.222
...you haven't held back with your games.

755
00:47:43.297 --> 00:47:45.925
What? Is that how you see it?

756
00:47:46.233 --> 00:47:47.598
I suppose.

757
00:47:49.770 --> 00:47:51.260
She's a witch.

758
00:47:52.239 --> 00:47:54.503
Yup, she's definitely "Auntie Witch".

759
00:47:58.045 --> 00:47:59.945
Hey, this painting...

760
00:48:00.180 --> 00:48:01.442
Recognize it?

761
00:48:01.515 --> 00:48:04.541
Yeah. It's the one
you've been restoring.


762
00:48:08.956 --> 00:48:10.821
It's a strange painting.

763
00:48:10.891 --> 00:48:14.691
The longer you look at it, the more
relaxed and comforted you feel.


764
00:48:15.896 --> 00:48:16.863
Yeah.

765
00:48:18.098 --> 00:48:20.066
We don't know who the painter is...

766
00:48:20.134 --> 00:48:23.661
...and we still don't really know
whether it has any artistic merit.


767
00:48:23.737 --> 00:48:27.696
But there's one thing I did learn
while working on its restoration.


