00:48:28.575 --> 00:48:30.566
This work was painted...

769
00:48:30.644 --> 00:48:34.205
...during a historical period of
famine and war many centuries ago.


770
00:48:34.915 --> 00:48:35.939
What?

771
00:48:36.583 --> 00:48:39.780
I wonder how someone was able
to paint such a thing...


772
00:48:39.853 --> 00:48:43.152
...while it seemed
the world was ending.


773
00:49:21.962 --> 00:49:24.021
What're you going to do, Konno?

774
00:49:24.098 --> 00:49:27.534
You're the only one that hasn't
submitted a chosen academic track.


775
00:49:28.302 --> 00:49:29.291
Konno...

776
00:49:29.636 --> 00:49:30.625
Hm?

777
00:49:30.704 --> 00:49:32.001
Konno...

778
00:49:33.240 --> 00:49:34.537
- Konno!
- Yes!


779
00:49:34.641 --> 00:49:36.472
Don't get cocky because
you did well on the...


780
00:49:36.543 --> 00:49:38.511
...practice college entrance exam.

781
00:49:38.579 --> 00:49:39.375
Yes, sir!

782
00:49:46.286 --> 00:49:47.878
That's weird...

783
00:49:49.423 --> 00:49:52.221
I swear it said "90" last time.

784
00:49:55.362 --> 00:49:57.421
I know. Why not ask her ourselves?

785
00:49:57.498 --> 00:49:58.590
Oh, but...

786
00:49:58.665 --> 00:50:01.156
- What?
- W-Wait!


787
00:50:01.235 --> 00:50:03.328
W
- Whoa! What's this about?!

788
00:50:03.403 --> 00:50:06.531
Miss Konno! We are members
of the Volunteer Club!


789
00:50:06.607 --> 00:50:08.871
And there's something
we'd like to ask you directly!


790
00:50:08.942 --> 00:50:10.341
I
- It's nothing!

791
00:50:10.410 --> 00:50:12.344
- We've noticed lately that...
- H-Hang on...


792
00:50:12.412 --> 00:50:13.845
- You're always with Kousuke!
- W-Wait!


793
00:50:13.914 --> 00:50:15.381
- I guess...
- Stop this!


794
00:50:15.449 --> 00:50:18.111
Does this mean that
you're going out with him?!


795
00:50:18.185 --> 00:50:19.550
Are you going out with him?

796
00:50:19.653 --> 00:50:21.587
Are you going out with him?!

797
00:50:27.294 --> 00:50:30.627
I was still in junior high
at the time...


798
00:50:30.697 --> 00:50:34.292
...but apparently, the Volunteer
Club of Kuranose Senior High...


799
00:50:34.368 --> 00:50:37.565
...once visited the old age home
that my grandmother was at.


800
00:50:37.638 --> 00:50:41.074
My grandmother was particularly
impressed with one of the...


801
00:50:41.141 --> 00:50:44.804
...students and she had
spoken to me about him many times.


802
00:50:44.878 --> 00:50:48.939
She would go on about what a kind
and gentle boy he was.


803
00:50:49.016 --> 00:50:51.610
She said it over and over.

804
00:50:52.219 --> 00:50:55.188
Since she had talked so
much about him...


805
00:50:55.255 --> 00:50:58.019
...I kind of began
to fall in love with him...


806
00:50:58.125 --> 00:51:02.789
...even though I'd never even met him.
- That's a cute story.


807
00:51:02.863 --> 00:51:05.229
I found out when
I got into senior high...


808
00:51:05.299 --> 00:51:08.700
...that the student was
Kousuke Tsuda.


809
00:51:08.769 --> 00:51:11.203
Wow, things like that really happen.

810
00:51:11.271 --> 00:51:14.297
But as you can see,
this girl is a total shrinking violet.


811
00:51:14.374 --> 00:51:16.569
We worked so hard
to pump her up.


812
00:51:16.643 --> 00:51:20.306
And we finally got her
to declare her feelings to him.


813
00:51:20.380 --> 00:51:21.472
Oh, the other day...

814
00:51:21.548 --> 00:51:23.482
But according to Kousuke...

815
00:51:23.550 --> 00:51:24.517
Huh? Hm?

816
00:51:25.552 --> 00:51:28.612
"I already have a girl that
I've given my heart to!"


817
00:51:28.689 --> 00:51:31.089
"So I'm sorry. 
I can't go out with you!"

818
00:51:31.158 --> 00:51:32.318
Um, but... wait...

819
00:51:32.392 --> 00:51:33.984
- But that's not how it went.
- Huh?


820
00:51:34.494 --> 00:51:37.986
"How could an idiot like that get
a higher mark than me?"


821
00:51:38.065 --> 00:51:40.499
"I can't be slacking off anymore, so... "

822
00:51:40.968 --> 00:51:42.833
And so he apologized.

823
00:51:47.174 --> 00:51:50.200
Could that "idiot"
he's referring to, be me?


824
00:51:50.277 --> 00:51:52.245
- And that's when Kousuke...
- Huh?!


825
00:51:52.312 --> 00:51:54.940
...said he wasn't going out
with you!


826
00:51:55.015 --> 00:51:57.074
But what has been
going on lately?!


827
00:51:57.150 --> 00:51:59.118
Something just doesn't seem right!

828
00:51:59.186 --> 00:52:00.847
Please explain properly!

829
00:52:00.921 --> 00:52:02.650
H
- Hang on a minute!

830
00:52:02.723 --> 00:52:04.691
O
- Okay! All right!

831
00:52:05.692 --> 00:52:08.525
Ahem! I'll deal with this somehow.

832
00:52:08.862 --> 00:52:09.794
Somehow?

833
00:52:09.963 --> 00:52:11.863
What do you mean, somehow?

834
00:52:12.199 --> 00:52:13.826
I'll deal with it somehow!

835
00:52:25.579 --> 00:52:26.375
Ow!

836
00:52:27.781 --> 00:52:30.579
- What the...?!
- What happened?


837
00:52:33.654 --> 00:52:35.485
Um... Well...

838
00:52:36.390 --> 00:52:37.357
Kaho!

839
00:52:37.958 --> 00:52:38.925
Yeah.

840
00:52:39.326 --> 00:52:40.293
Um...

841
00:52:41.395 --> 00:52:42.384
Kousuke!

842
00:52:43.797 --> 00:52:44.764
Huh?

843
00:52:46.833 --> 00:52:50.599
What? Didn't you just head off
to the baseball field?!


844
00:52:50.671 --> 00:52:51.865
Never mind that!

845
00:52:51.939 --> 00:52:55.500
This girl's grandmother says she's
so grateful that you came around...


846
00:52:55.575 --> 00:52:57.770
...and took care of her at
the old age home.


847
00:52:57.844 --> 00:52:59.607
I'm impressed, Kousuke!
And, you see...


848
00:52:59.680 --> 00:53:03.241
H
- How do you know my grandmother?!

849
00:53:03.317 --> 00:53:06.445
How? Um, I met
her at the bowling alley...


850
00:53:06.520 --> 00:53:08.078
My grandmother's bedridden!

851
00:53:08.155 --> 00:53:09.622
Oh! That's not it...!

852
00:53:09.690 --> 00:53:11.555
Let me know when you're
done talking.


853
00:53:11.625 --> 00:53:13.820
Uh, w-wait, Kousuke!

854
00:53:16.897 --> 00:53:18.091
What the...?!

855
00:53:20.734 --> 00:53:21.792
One more time!

856
00:53:28.241 --> 00:53:29.037
Ow!

857
00:53:30.477 --> 00:53:31.774
Um... Well...

858
00:53:33.146 --> 00:53:34.113
Kousuke!

859
00:53:35.382 --> 00:53:36.246
Huh?

860
00:53:37.284 --> 00:53:38.251
Here we go...

861
00:53:38.318 --> 00:53:40.912
- What? Didn't you just head off...?!
- Hold it!


862
00:53:40.988 --> 00:53:42.717
You're being very cowardly about this!

863
00:53:42.789 --> 00:53:44.882
Don't sulk about
me getting a better mark!


864
00:53:44.958 --> 00:53:46.949
This has nothing to do with that!

865
00:53:47.027 --> 00:53:49.427
What's up with you, showing up
out of nowhere and bragging?!


866
00:53:49.496 --> 00:53:50.963
And this has nothing to do
with what?!


867
00:53:51.031 --> 00:53:54.262
I'm saying that my test score
should have nothing to do with...


868
00:53:54.334 --> 00:53:56.063
...Kaho being in love with you!

869
00:53:56.136 --> 00:53:57.694
- Th-That's not true!
- What?!


870
00:53:57.771 --> 00:53:59.102
That's not true!

871
00:53:59.172 --> 00:54:01.299
- W-Wait! Kaho!
- Kaho!


872
00:54:01.375 --> 00:54:04.572
- She says it's not true.
- Uh! Hang on, Kousuke!


873
00:54:07.547 --> 00:54:09.071
What the...?!

874
00:54:12.786 --> 00:54:15.482
I've got to take
a more basic approach to this.


875
00:54:28.502 --> 00:54:31.835
Why all the ruckus so early
in the morning, sis?


876
00:54:31.905 --> 00:54:35.033
I went back too far!
And I'm late, to boot! Aww!


877
00:54:35.108 --> 00:54:36.837
Makoto! The peaches!

878
00:54:37.477 --> 00:54:38.569
The peaches!

879
00:54:42.883 --> 00:54:43.679
Huh?

880
00:54:48.155 --> 00:54:49.144
Oh, boy...

881
00:54:49.790 --> 00:54:51.485
And for the headlock!

882
00:54:53.794 --> 00:54:54.590
Ha!

883
00:54:55.195 --> 00:54:56.628
Huh? What was that?

884
00:54:56.696 --> 00:54:57.663
Amazing...

885
00:54:57.731 --> 00:54:59.665
- Don't look. Just carry on!
- Huh?


886
00:54:59.733 --> 00:55:01.030
You guys need to move!

887
00:55:01.101 --> 00:55:01.800
Year 1 Class 2

888
00:55:01.835 --> 00:55:02.824
Year 1 Class 2
Kaho!


889
00:55:03.070 --> 00:55:03.866
Huh?

890
00:55:03.937 --> 00:55:05.131
I don't exactly know why...

891
00:55:05.205 --> 00:55:07.366
...but she wants you to come
down to the courtyard.


892
00:55:07.441 --> 00:55:08.806
Who does?

893
00:55:08.875 --> 00:55:11.901
Where are we going?!
What're you going to make me do?!


894
00:55:11.978 --> 00:55:14.310
- You'll know when we get there!
- Makoto!


895
00:55:14.381 --> 00:55:15.370
Later!

896
00:55:15.449 --> 00:55:16.916
Okay! Okay! You got me!

897
00:55:17.250 --> 00:55:19.810
Is this what she meant by
"come to the courtyard"?


898
00:55:19.886 --> 00:55:20.784
Who knows?

899
00:55:23.590 --> 00:55:26.388
- Go there!
- Uh, wha...?


900
00:55:29.296 --> 00:55:30.695
That was close!

901
00:55:31.798 --> 00:55:33.288
Ow, ow...!

902
00:55:33.366 --> 00:55:36.028
What the hell are you
guys doing?!


903
00:55:36.570 --> 00:55:38.629
- You're hurting me.
- Huh?


904
00:55:39.673 --> 00:55:40.640
Ah! Oh, no!

905
00:55:42.209 --> 00:55:43.733
- Can you get up?
- Yeah.


906
00:55:45.045 --> 00:55:46.012
Oh!

907
00:55:46.079 --> 00:55:48.877
- You might've sprained it.
- Oh, I'm fine. It's okay.


908
00:55:48.949 --> 00:55:51.816
- It's not okay!
- K-Kousuke!


909
00:55:52.285 --> 00:55:55.686
- Put your hand over my shoulder.
- I-I'm sorry...


910
00:55:56.056 --> 00:55:59.958
- What do you think of this development?
- This could be...


911
00:56:00.026 --> 00:56:01.994
This could be something!

912
00:56:02.062 --> 00:56:02.926
All right!

913
00:56:04.431 --> 00:56:07.093
I sure feel like I did something good!

914
00:56:07.167 --> 00:56:09.533
Oh, what a happy feeling this is!

915
00:56:11.304 --> 00:56:12.100
Hm?

916
00:56:12.172 --> 00:56:13.867
It's changed again!

917
00:56:13.940 --> 00:56:16.534
Ten? What does "10" mean?

918
00:56:18.345 --> 00:56:19.312
Hm?

919
00:56:20.180 --> 00:56:21.147
One?

920
00:57:22.709 --> 00:57:26.076
No one's here.
Maybe I'm too early.


921
00:57:34.821 --> 00:57:37.381
There he is...

922
00:57:50.537 --> 00:57:53.335
Um, excuse me!
I have a question for you!


923
00:57:56.209 --> 00:57:57.506
Yuri!

924
00:57:57.577 --> 00:57:59.568
I was wondering who it was.

925
00:57:59.646 --> 00:58:01.045
Why...?

926
00:58:01.248 --> 00:58:03.876
I brought the notebooks up for you.

927
00:58:03.950 --> 00:58:06.544
I think you forgot
you had duties today.


928
00:58:06.620 --> 00:58:08.349
Oh! That's right!

929
00:58:08.421 --> 00:58:09.979
I figured as much.

930
00:58:10.056 --> 00:58:12.490
I hope you appreciate our
friendship here.


931
00:58:12.559 --> 00:58:14.390
So, what's your question?

932
00:58:14.461 --> 00:58:16.292
Oh, uh, it's nothing!

933
00:58:16.363 --> 00:58:17.330
Fine.

934
00:58:22.035 --> 00:58:24.003
- Hey, Yuri...
- Hm?


935
00:58:24.070 --> 00:58:26.436
Did you see anyone
on your way up here?


936
00:58:26.506 --> 00:58:27.530
Like who?

937
00:58:27.607 --> 00:58:29.541
Uh, never mind.

938
00:58:30.577 --> 00:58:31.544
All right.

939
00:58:37.050 --> 00:58:37.482
Mailbox: I think I was just
asked out. I bet you're envious!


940
00:58:37.517 --> 00:58:41.421
Mailbox: I think I was just asked out. I bet you're
envious! From Kousuke... "I think I was just asked out. "


941
00:58:41.454 --> 00:58:43.012
Mailbox: I'm borrowing your bike.
- Tsuda Huh?


942
00:58:43.590 --> 00:58:46.559
Oh, please... Who do
you think set it up for you?


943
00:58:48.228 --> 00:58:51.994
I'm borrowing your bike.
- Tsuda


944
00:58:52.565 --> 00:58:54.055
Don't tell me...

945
00:58:55.669 --> 00:58:57.364
Ma...

946
00:58:57.437 --> 00:58:58.734
Ko...

947
00:58:58.805 --> 00:59:00.534
To... There.

948
00:59:00.607 --> 00:59:01.699
Where do you live?

949
00:59:01.775 --> 00:59:03.902
In the south district,
on the other side of the station.


950
00:59:03.977 --> 00:59:06.275
We should probably
go by the hospital.


951
00:59:06.346 --> 00:59:08.871
- What?
- My place is close by.


952
00:59:09.883 --> 00:59:11.874
Makoto, come to think of it...

953
00:59:12.185 --> 00:59:14.949
I passed by a
guy on my way here...

954
00:59:17.390 --> 00:59:18.880
It was Chiaki.

955
00:59:22.529 --> 00:59:23.587
Kousuke!

956
00:59:23.963 --> 00:59:27.330
He went home.
Holding hands with that first year girl.


957
00:59:30.303 --> 00:59:31.270
It's gone!

958
00:59:38.278 --> 00:59:39.438
Hey, Kousuke!

959
00:59:39.879 --> 00:59:44.782
Yeah, it's me. Hey, Dad,
I've got a sprain. Think you can fix it?


960
00:59:44.851 --> 00:59:46.478
Oh, it's not me.

961
00:59:47.053 --> 00:59:48.611
Yeah, right away.

962
00:59:49.089 --> 00:59:50.386
I'm sorry.

963
00:59:50.457 --> 00:59:52.982
Please leave a message
after the beep.


964
00:59:53.059 --> 00:59:54.026
Damn!

965
01:00:06.172 --> 01:00:09.437
What should I do?
Should I go back in time?


966
01:00:09.509 --> 01:00:12.478
But it's not like
anything's happened yet.


967
01:00:51.551 --> 01:00:52.074
Huh?

968
01:00:52.519 --> 01:00:53.076
Hm?

969
01:01:05.432 --> 01:01:09.732
Uh, um... Was there
a bike accident here?


970
01:01:09.803 --> 01:01:12.704
No. I don't think so.

971
01:01:13.173 --> 01:01:14.640
Thank you.

972
01:01:14.707 --> 01:01:17.699
An accident, she says. How scary.

973
01:01:21.981 --> 01:01:24.541
Kousuke? Where are you now?
Kousuke?


974
01:01:30.723 --> 01:01:31.951
Chiaki.

975
01:01:34.928 --> 01:01:37.226
Kousuke's over at his place.

976
01:01:37.297 --> 01:01:39.265
You guys didn't show up at the field!

977
01:01:39.332 --> 01:01:40.890
- Sorry.
- I'll be waiting.


978
01:01:40.967 --> 01:01:42.594
- Hey, you know...
- Huh?


979
01:01:42.669 --> 01:01:47.231
I've been wanting to ask you
something for a while now.


980
01:01:48.308 --> 01:01:50.776
Do you have fun playing
baseball with me?


981
01:01:50.844 --> 01:01:54.780
- What're you talking about?
- I like playing baseball with you.


982
01:01:54.848 --> 01:01:57.942
For someone who likes baseball,
you sure don't improve much.


983
01:01:58.017 --> 01:01:59.814
Well, all you've got is enthusiasm.

984
01:01:59.886 --> 01:02:01.786
Better than having none.

985
01:02:03.590 --> 01:02:05.751
What are you laughing about?

986
01:02:07.026 --> 01:02:10.052
It feels like I'm talking to you
for the first time in a while.


987
01:02:10.129 --> 01:02:12.461
What're you talking about?
We've been talking all day.


988
01:02:12.532 --> 01:02:14.932
Oh, right. I guess.

989
01:02:15.001 --> 01:02:18.027
- You miss me that much?
- W-What're you talking about, stupid?!


990
01:02:18.104 --> 01:02:20.436
Just kidding! Come on!

991
01:02:22.876 --> 01:02:26.744
Actually, there's something
I wanted to ask you as well.


992
01:02:26.813 --> 01:02:27.745
What's that?

993
01:02:27.814 --> 01:02:29.782
It's a really stupid question.

994
01:02:29.849 --> 01:02:31.441
Well, what is it?

995
01:02:32.752 --> 01:02:35.448
- Well...
- Come on. Spit it out.


996
01:02:36.523 --> 01:02:39.492
Have you been time leaping?

997
01:02:45.965 --> 01:02:48.297
You've been time leaping,
haven't you?


998
01:02:49.969 --> 01:02:51.231
Hey, Makoto...

999
01:02:52.071 --> 01:02:53.231
Makoto!

1000
01:02:58.311 --> 01:03:02.805
Actually, there's something
I wanted to ask you as well.


1001
01:03:03.249 --> 01:03:06.116
It's a really stupid question.

1002
01:03:06.953 --> 01:03:08.853
- Well...
- H-Hang on a second!


1003
01:03:08.922 --> 01:03:10.856
- Huh?
- Let's talk about my little sister.


1004
01:03:10.924 --> 01:03:14.257
- Huh? Why?
- You see, my sister is really stupid...!


1005
01:03:14.327 --> 01:03:16.488
Hold on, I was about to...

1006
01:03:19.065 --> 01:03:21.829
Never mind. I'll be waiting then.

1007
01:03:24.370 --> 01:03:26.338
How does Chiaki know...?

1008
01:03:28.808 --> 01:03:29.775
Hm?

1009
01:03:30.376 --> 01:03:33.675
Z ero? So these numbers did
represent the number of times...


1010
01:03:33.746 --> 01:03:34.770
...I could time leap.

1011
01:03:35.448 --> 01:03:38.474
I sure wasted my last one
on something lame.


1012
01:03:38.551 --> 01:03:42.180
Oh, well. I guess it's okay,
seeing that Kousuke's all right.


1013
01:03:42.322 --> 01:03:43.516
Hey, Makoto!

1014
01:03:53.366 --> 01:03:55.334
I need to borrow this a bit longer!

1015
01:03:57.937 --> 01:03:59.564
Wait, Kousuke!

1016
01:03:59.639 --> 01:04:00.663
Kousu...!

1017
01:04:03.042 --> 01:04:06.910
Hey! Watch where you're going!
Apologize now! Hey!


1018
01:04:07.280 --> 01:04:08.247
Look!

